  "prompt": "Can you get cocaine out of your system in 24?",
  "response": "Getting cocaine out of your system in 24 hours is unlikely, as the elimination of cocaine and its metabolites from the body depends on several factors, including the amount used, frequency of use, individual metabolism, and overall health. Typically, cocaine can be detected in the blood or urine for up to several days after use.\n\nCocaine has a short half-life, approximately 1 hour, and its metabolites, like benzoylecgonine, can be detected for a longer period. Benzoylecgonine, which is the primary metabolite of cocaine, can be detected in urine for up to 3 to 4 days for occasional users and up to 2 weeks for chronic users. Blood and saliva tests may detect cocaine for up to 24 to 48 hours, while hair tests can reveal cocaine use for months.\n\nIt's important to recognize that trying to expedite the removal of cocaine from your system can be dangerous and is not recommended. If you are concerned about cocaine use, it's best to seek professional medical help and support.",
